text: Cintia Rodríguez Rodríguez (born November 16, 1994) is a Spanish artistic gymnast. She helped Spain qualify a women's team for the 2020 Summer Olympics through her performances at the 2019 World Artistic Gymnastics Championships, marking the first time Spain have sent a women's team since Athens 2004.https://www.gymnastics.sport/site/events/detail.php?id=15571#loaded Rodriguez studies criminology through the National University of Distance Education. == References == ==External links== * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Spanish female artistic gymnasts Category:People from Mallorca Category:Spanish criminologists
